# Frontend Rules

## Purpose
Consistent Next.js App Router UI per `docs/UI_UX_GUIDELINES.md` and RBAC visibility.

## Requirements
- TypeScript strict; shadcn/ui + Tailwind for components.
- Feature-based folders under `features/`.
- TanStack Query for client data; server components for public SEO pages.
- React Hook Form + Zod for all forms.
- Permission-gate UI from `/auth/me` permissions — hide unauthorized actions.
- INR currency formatting utility; E.164 phone display.

## Restrictions
- No secrets in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`.
- No storing JWT in localStorage (prefer httpOnly cookie pattern from API).
- No inline styles except dynamic values.
- Client role must not display internal IDs or commission fields.

## Best Practices
- Skeleton loaders for tables; optimistic updates for stage changes with rollback.
- Error boundaries on feature routes.
- Image `next/image` with dimensions for LCP.
- i18n-ready strings (English MVP).

## Anti-Patterns
- Fetch in every component without query cache.
- 500-line page components — split into features.
- Hardcoded tenant slug.

## Examples

```tsx
// GOOD: Permission-gated button
{permissions.includes('properties.delete') && (
  <Button variant="destructive" onClick={handleDelete}>Delete</Button>
)}
```
